Eligible: Extensive SCLC, 4 cycles of first-line platinum chemo completed with CR. Brain metastases were treated and are stable (no continuous steroids/anticonvulsants). ECOG 0. All lab parameters (hepatic, renal, hematologic) meet the requirements.

Eligible: Extensive SCLC (mixed histology, $\ge 80\%$ SCLC), achieved PR after 4 cycles. ECOG 1. Has liver metastases, so AST/ALT $\le 5.0\times$ ULN is allowed and met (exactly 5.0). All other lab parameters are at the minimum/maximum threshold (1.5$\times$ ULN for non-hepatic, minimum hematologic counts), and contraception requirements are met.
Eligible: Extensive SCLC, achieved PR, ECOG 0. Brain mets treated and stable. Meets all organ function and hematology criteria well within limits (AST/ALT $\le 2.5\times$ ULN for no liver mets).
Eligible: Extensive SCLC, achieved CR after 4 cycles. Has liver mets, AST/ALT $4.0\times$ ULN (allowed, $\le 5.0\times$ ULN). Meets all hematologic minimums and contraception requirements.
Eligible: Extensive SCLC, achieved PR, ECOG 1. No liver mets, AST/ALT $2.2\times$ ULN (allowed, $\le 2.5\times$ ULN). Meets all lab criteria with a wide margin.
Eligible: Advanced lung adenocarcinoma with EGFR mutation, prior erlotinib response then progression, adequate organ function, no cardiac contraindications, QTc normal.
Eligible: EGFR-mutant adenocarcinoma with prior gefitinib response then resistance, asymptomatic CNS lesions, excellent performance status, all labs within range.
Eligible: Elderly patient with EGFR-mutant adenocarcinoma, prior TKI response then progression, adequate washout from prior therapies, meets all lab criteria.
Eligible: EGFR-mutant adenocarcinoma with gefitinib response then acquired resistance, stable asymptomatic brain mets, all hematologic and cardiac parameters acceptable.
Eligible: Advanced EGFR-mutant adenocarcinoma with prior erlotinib complete response then progression, adequate treatment washout, normal QTc, no exclusion criteria.

Eligible: Metastatic Colorectal Cancer (HLA-A2.1/p53+), ECOG 1, life expectancy $>3$ months. All washout periods met ($\ge 4-8$ weeks), meets all hematologic/organ function/coagulation criteria. Cardiac status is NYHA Class I, no history of ventricular arrhythmias/recent MI/CHF, and passed required cardiac stress test. Pulmonary function normal, no CNS disease, systemic steroids, or active infection.

Eligible: Locally Advanced Breast Cancer (HLA-A2.1/p53+), ECOG 0. Meets all washout, lab, and organ function criteria. Cardiac status is NYHA Class II (allowed), no history of ventricular arrhythmias/recent MI/CHF. Not pregnant/nursing and using effective contraception.

Eligible: Metastatic RCC (HLA-A2.1/p53+), life expectancy exactly 3 months (minimum). Meets all minimum hematologic/organ function/coagulation cutoffs. Cardiac stress test required due to age $>50$ and FEV1 exactly $75\%$ of predicted (minimum for PFT). No prior IL-2, CNS disease, or autoimmune disease.

Eligible: Metastatic Ovarian Cancer (HLA-A2.1/p53+), ECOG 0. Excellent organ function and cardiac status. Meets all washout criteria (especially Mab, $>8$ weeks), not on chronic asthma meds, and using effective contraception.

Eligible: Metastatic Pancreatic Cancer (HLA-A2.1/p53+), ECOG 1. All washouts met. Stress test required due to age $>50$ and is normal. No systemic steroids, no investigational agents, and no history of HIV or prior allograft.

Eligible: Ovarian Cancer (allowed in escalation). QTcF $<470$ msec, no history of CNS mets/meningitis, no uncontrolled active infection, no serious unresolved toxicities from prior treatment, and no pulmonary or corneal exclusions.
Eligible: Endometrial Cancer (allowed in optimization). QTcF $\le 470$ msec, no significant cardiovascular disease, no history of pneumonitis/ILD, and no history of corneal issues.
Eligible: NSCLC (allowed in expansion). Meets all cardiac and CNS exclusion criteria. All prior toxicities are resolved, and no active uncontrolled infection.
Eligible: TNBC (allowed in expansion). QTcF well below threshold, no CNS/pulmonary/cardiac contraindications. Not pregnant/breastfeeding and using effective contraception.
Eligible: Pancreatic Cancer (allowed in escalation). QTcF is high but $\le 470$ msec (allowed). No corneal, infection, or CNS exclusions apply.
Eligible: ES-SCLC Stage IV progressed during first-line platinum therapy, tissue available for organoid culture, stable CNS mets, adequate organ function.
Eligible: ES-SCLC with progression within 6 months of first-line platinum, malignant effusion available for organoids, excellent performance status, no CNS disease.
Eligible: Elderly ES-SCLC patient with progression on first-line platinum, adequate biopsy tissue, stable brain metastases, meets all functional criteria.
Eligible: ES-SCLC progressed post-platinum therapy, malignant effusion available, excellent ECOG 0, no prior second-line treatment, compliant.
Eligible: ES-SCLC with progression during first-line platinum, sufficient biopsy tissue for organoids, adequate performance status, no exclusion criteria.
